cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of finding correspondences between image patches from different modalities, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed TS-Net architecture combines the benefits of both Siamese and Pseudo-Siamese approaches, which involves deep learning techniques (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents experimental results on multimodal datasets, which involves machine learning (cs.ML) and neural networks (cs.NE).
